{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-accipiter-rufiventris", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-accipiter-rufiventris", "name": "Rufous-breasted sparrowhawk", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "bird-rufous-breasted-sparrowhawk-8cd733e1", "name": "Rufous-breasted sparrowhawk", "englishName": "Rufous-breasted sparrowhawk", "latinName": "Accipiter rufiventris", "type": "bird", "status": "LC", "summary": "The rufous-breasted sparrowhawk (Accipiter rufiventris), also known as the rufous-chested sparrowhawk and as the red-breasted sparrowhawk, is a species of bird of prey in the family Accipitridae. It is found in Angola, Democratic Republic of the Congo, Eritrea, Eswatini, Ethiopia, Kenya, Lesotho, Malawi, Mozambique, Rwanda, South Africa, South Sudan, Tanzania, Uganda, Zambia, and Zimbabwe. Description A small raptor, with a height of about 30 cm and wingspan of 72 cm, the rufous-breasted sparrowhawk is named for its distinctive rufous-coloured underparts, which can be seen both perching and in flight. It is dark grey slate-brown above, including the head, with a black bill and eyes that are yellow at all ages. In flight, the bold bars on both its wings and tail are clearly visible. Juvenile plumage ranges from the rufous-color of adults to more white, but all have feathers with dark shaft streaks on their underside. It can be differentiated from the similar Ovambo sparrowhawk (Accipiter ovampensis) by its lack of a dark patch behind the eyes or white eyebrow. Taxonomy The rufous-breasted sparrowhawk is in the family Accipitridae, and is a part of the genus Accipiter, which contains sparrowhawks, goshawks, and other small woodland hawks. Within this genus it forms a superspecies with the Eurasian sparrowhawk (A. nisus) and possibly the Madagascar sparrowhawk (A. madagascariensis) (Ferguson-Lees and Christie 2001). Recent DNA barcoding research found it to be potentially conspecific with A. nisus, but did not support a superspecies with A. madagascariensis. Habitat and distribution The rufous-breasted sparrowhawk has the most restricted range of any southern African accipiter, though it has expanded with the introduction of non-native pine species. It occupies montane forest habitats from the Cape of Good Hope to the Ethiopian highlands, though locally its range is quite small and divided between forest patches. Behavior The rufous-breasted sparrowhawk shares many behavioral qualities with other African and European accipiters, but virtually nothing is known of its diet and nestling development. Vocalization Its call is a series of high, fast \"kew\" notes, with the male being higher-pitched than the female. A more drawn out \"kieee-u\" is made by the female to request food from the nearby male, and is adopted by the young as a begging call whenever adults are near. Diet Usually hunts on the wing for doves and other small birds, but may occasionally strike from a perch to feed on insects, small mammals (including bats) and reptiles. Reproduction Undergoes courtship by flying very high above the nesting area and calling, and mating often occurs after the male presents the female with an offer of food. Nests are platforms built from small sticks 6-18m above the ground, and are built by snapping off sticks in flight with their talons or by breaking them with their beak. A new nest is usually built each year, though often very close to the previous nesting site. Two to four eggs are laid in September and October, and are white with red-brown blotches that coalesce in a cap. Incubation is undergone primarily by the female, while the male fetches food, which is given to her in a nearby tree. References Ferguson-Lees, James and David A. Christie (2001) Raptors of the World. Christopher Helm, London. pp. 578–581. ISBN 0-7136-8026-1 Images from African Bird Club External links (Rufous-breasted Sparrowhawk = ) Red-breasted Sparrowhawk - Species text in The Atlas of Southern African Birds", "shortSummary": "The rufous-breasted sparrowhawk (Accipiter rufiventris), also known as the rufous-chested sparrowhawk and as the red-breasted sparrowhawk,…", "locations": ["安哥拉", "刚果民主共和国", "厄立特里亚", "史瓦帝尼", "莱索托", "马拉维", "莫桑比克", "卢旺达", "南蘇丹", "乌干达", "赞比亚", "辛巴威"], "lat": -12.5, "lng": 18.5, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d0/Rufous-chested_Sparrowhawk_%28Accipiter_rufiventris%29.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-accipiter", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-accipiter-rufiventris", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-accipiter", "species": "taxonomy-species-accipiter-rufiventris"}, "expandable": true, "x": -503.19, "y": -280.6, "z": -402.91}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-accipiter", "name": "Accipiter", "latinName": "Accipiter", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Accipiter（Accipiter）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联6种鸟类，如Grey-bellied hawk、Madagascar sparrowhawk、Ovambo sparrowhawk等6种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 6, "x": -305.61, "y": 458.04, "z": 48.16}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-accipiter-rufiventris", "name": "Rufous-breasted sparrowhawk", "latinName": "Accipiter rufiventris", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Rufous-breasted sparrowhawk（Accipiter rufiventris）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Rufous-breasted sparrowhawk。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": -503.19, "y": -280.6, "z": -390.82}], "links": [{"key": "bird-rufous-breasted-sparrowhawk-8cd733e1__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-accipiter-rufiventris", "source": "bird-rufous-breasted-sparrowhawk-8cd733e1", "target": "taxonomy-species-accipiter-rufiventris", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-accipiter-rufiventris__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-accipiter", "source": "taxonomy-species-accipiter-rufiventris", "target": "taxonomy-genus-accipiter", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：Rufous-breasted sparrowhawk 属于属 Accipiter。"}]}
